mid...</span><hr size=1> ... but I rerolled Amabutho. I think he was sworn to Ullycia. He's at the tent now, so I'll re-swear him next time I see Dia. Sorry if this screwed anything up, but I got really frustrated with the way Ghar Jr. was turning out.<br>
<br>
I learned a lot from Junior, but I think he was fatally flawed. With melee D only trained, and low quickness, he was taking a beating. The new Amabutho is another axe guy, started him 100-10-80-30-100-10, with axe, life, and arcane specialized, and healing and mana C trained. He's going to be painful to start, with no melee D until 12, and no item until 32. But hopefully after that he'll be a pretty strong character... he'll have low melee D like Jr, but with spec life and high focus, he should be able to imperil/vuln stuff, which should make up for it. We'll see!<br>
